snippet.title: How to tell if amber is genuine – with Dr Ricardo Pérez-de la Fuente
snippet.description:
Our researchers often get given items, but how do they know that those items are genuine? Dr Ricardo Pérez-de la Fuente, a researcher here at the Oxford University Museum of Natural History, discusses how to test amber to determine its authenticity.
Find out more on our website www.oumnh.ox.ac.uk and https://oumnh.web.ox.ac.uk/research-0 

Got a question for any of our research staff, or about the Museum? Leave a comment below or contact us on social media and we'll pass it on!

The last three images in this video can be found in these open access journals: 
https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/pala.12414
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3391719/
https://www.biotaxa.org/pe/article/view/palaeoentomology.2.3.13
